PUFFIN BEAM FILE

Describes electron beams for input into puffin. Multiple beams with
different parameters can be used. Please refer to POP-REF for an
explanation of the scaled variables used, such as z2 and p2.

1         # of beams

READ IN BEAM CHARACTERISTICS
========================================================================
BEAM 1:-

STANDARD DEVIATION OF BEAM IN EACH DIMENSION (=1E8 FOR FLAT TOP)   - REAL

1.0                 SIGX       (overwritten for matched beam)
1.0                 SIGY       (overwritten for matched beam)
1E8                 SIGZ2
1E-6                SIGPX      (overwritten for matched beam)
1E-6                SIGPY      (overwritten for matched beam)
1E-6                SIGGAMMA

TOTAL MODELLED LENGTH OF BEAM IN EACH DIMENSION    - REAL

1E-6                 LENX       (overwritten for matched beam)
1E-6                 LENY       (overwritten for matched beam)
20.0                 LENZ2
1E-6                LENPX      (overwritten for matched beam)
1E-6                LENPY      (overwritten for matched beam)
1E-6                LENGAMMA

NUMBER OF MACROPARTICLES TO MODEL BEAM IN EACH DIMENSION (EQUISPACED BEFORE NOISE IS ADDED, IF USED)   - INTEGER

1                  NUMX
1                  NUMY
8000                NUMZ2
1                  NUMPX
1                  NUMPY
1                  NUMGAMMA

BEAM PARAMETERS

.FALSE.              Match beam to undulator?
1.0                 Ratio of average beam energy to resonant beam energy gamma / gamma_r
1.0                 Scaled emittance (\bar{epsilon})
0.0                 Energy chirp in z2 i.e. dgamma/dz2
0.0                 Center of beam in z2
1.0E-9              Charge in coulombs
